p: Geisinger Health System patients living with HBV were reported to PDoH, 88.4% (152 of 172) of the time ( Table 1). The adjusted percentage of Geisinger Health System patients living with HBV that were reported to PDoH, was 82.6% ( Table 1). Further, none of the select patient characteristics: gender, age group, race/ethnicity, rural-urban classification, or initial_diagnosis_year, were found to be statistically associated with a HBV infected patientâ€™s infection going unreported to PDoH ( Table 1).
